about.summary: The configuration format defined by 'TOML' (which expands to "Tom's Obvious Markup Language") specifies an excellent format (described at <https://github.com/toml-lang/toml>) suitable for both human editing as well as the common uses of a machine-readable format. This package uses 'Rcpp' to connect the 'cpptoml' parser written by Chase Geigle (in modern C++11) to R.

name: r-rcpptoml
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '0.1.6' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-rcpptoml
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/RcppTOML_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/RcppTOML/RcppTOML_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 7a0d5e60da4dfaab684c927ed5a15c80e83882fc3600ec7f661b419fad27dbdb

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 2
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}              # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}            # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_cxx') }}      # [win]
    - {{ posix }}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}make
    - {{ posix }}sed               # [win]
    - {{ posix }}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-rcpp >=0.11.5
  run:
    - r-base
    - {{ native }}gcc-libs         # [win]
    - r-rcpp >=0.11.5

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('RcppTOML')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('RcppTOML')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: http://dirk.eddelbuettel.com/code/rcpp.toml.html
  license: GPL (>= 2)
  summary: The configuration format defined by 'TOML' (which expands to "Tom's Obvious Markup
    Language") specifies an excellent format (described at <https://github.com/toml-lang/toml>)
    suitable for both human editing as well as the common uses of a machine-readable
    format. This package uses 'Rcpp' to connect the 'cpptoml' parser written by Chase
    Geigle (in modern C++11) to R.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
